---
By: Lao Tzu
Source:
  URL: "https://web.archive.org/web/20140511202128/\
    http://my.pclink.com:80/~allchin/tao/contents.htm"
  Locus:
    Date: 20 August 2017
    Chapter: 68
  Copyright: 2002
  Translator: Douglas Allchin
---
Who battles well
is free of aggression.
Who fights well
is free of anger.
Who conquers his enemy
is free of encounter.
Who wins over others
is free of arrogance.
Such is integrity with no contention.
Such is finding advantage in others.
Such is meeting with heaven,
long since the ultimate.
